I mean, it's like
this combination--

00:23:21.760 --> 00:23:23.420
I call it a talent avalanche.

00:23:23.420 --> 00:23:25.760
It's just, you could
watch it a million times.

00:23:25.760 --> 00:23:26.980
MICHAEL SHAYAN: Now they're
going to pass you $20.

00:23:26.980 --> 00:23:27.830
DAVID YAZBEK: I
would like that $20.

00:23:27.830 --> 00:23:28.830
[LAUGHTER]

00:23:29.702 --> 00:23:31.910
MICHAEL SHAYAN: Katrina
actually has a beautiful song

00:23:31.910 --> 00:23:35.510
in the show about Umm
Kulthum and we are

00:23:35.510 --> 00:23:37.610
going to hear it in a minute.

00:23:37.610 --> 00:23:39.110
DAVID CROMER: Well,
I was just going

00:23:39.110 --> 00:23:45.980
to say that at sort of the
center point of the show, one

00:23:45.980 --> 00:23:48.320
of the-- the Egyptian
band leader character

00:23:48.320 --> 00:23:50.519
and Katrina's character,
who's an Israeli cafe owner

00:23:50.519 --> 00:23:52.310
are having kind of an
awkward conversation,

00:23:52.310 --> 00:23:53.780
and trying to find their
way to conversation.

00:23:53.780 --> 00:23:55.730
And like in many
conversations in this show,

00:23:55.730 --> 00:23:59.120
they're able to find their
way to it by he accidentally

00:23:59.120 --> 00:24:01.020
mentions that he plays
classical Arab music.

00:24:01.020 --> 00:24:02.960
And she says, oh,
like Umm Kulthum?

00:24:02.960 --> 00:24:04.040
And he says, oh, yeah.

00:24:04.040 --> 00:24:05.370
And she goes, oh, I love that.

00:24:05.370 --> 00:24:06.580
And he says, no, come on.

00:24:06.580 --> 00:24:08.480
You don't-- he says
you're being polite.

00:24:08.480 --> 00:24:10.530
Don't-- you know, and she--

00:24:10.530 --> 00:24:13.160
it actually accessed
something in her life

00:24:13.160 --> 00:24:15.230
that she cared about
